******
[1] Madison County, New York
Date: Thu 11 Sep 2014
Source: Time Warner Cable News [edited]
http://centralny.twcnews.com/content/news/768320/horse-in-madison-county-dies-from-eee-virus/


A horse in Madison County [New York] has died from the eastern equine encephalitis virus (EEE).

Health officials said the horse was stabled in the Town of Lenox -- which is outside the area known to harbor the virus.

Horses are vulnerable to EEE, but there is a vaccine available to protect horses from it.

County health officials said an infected horse cannot pass the virus to other animals or people.

According to the New York State Department of Health, EEE is spread by mosquitoes and can affect people and horses.

--
